section_videos.video_title: Exploring Guitar Wisdom 2022
section_videos.video_description:
Explore Guitar Wisdom. The easiest way is to click BROWSE, then "View all" and "Show more" to see each playlist/category in its entirety.
If you are a beginner, we recommend that you start with the Beginner Series and the Sight-Reading Series. Both of these Series are arranged sequentially, so that you can follow an established path at the outset.
Guitarists with some playing experience may want to jump into the Foundation & Technique series and Music Theory I. These lessons are  linear/sequential at the beginning, but they transition to topical lessons.
The lessons on Blues, Jazz, Funk, R&B and Improvisation are topical. They are not meant to be followed in any strict order.

There are many paths to wisdom! The most important thing is to find the one that is right for you! 
If you are a subscriber, and you need some ideas for creating your own path here, please check out Tomo's video on "How to Learn with Guitar Wisdom" (QAP02) in the Q&A/Proficiency section.

section_videos.video_title: B1 Open Chord - E minor, Guitar Basics, Picking, Strumming
section_videos.video_description: Your first open chord: E minor. Learn a simple, open chord. Learn the notes of the open strings. Learn the proper way to hold your pick. Learn rhythm basics and strum in 4/4 time: whole notes, half notes and quarter notes. Guitar: Harmony acoustic with pickup. BOSS Katana 50 amp. D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature.

section_videos.video_title: B2 Open Chord - D - Arpeggio - Alternate Picking
section_videos.video_description: Learn the triangle-shaped open D chord on Strings 4 3 2 1. In 4/4 time, strum the D chord or play an arpeggio. Learn to pick with downward and upward strokes. Learn to use alternate picking, when playing eighth notes. Guitar: Harmony acoustic with pickup. BOSS Katana 50 amp. D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature.

section_videos.video_title: B3 Open Chord - C - Strumming Patterns

section_videos.video_title: B4 Open Chord - G - Strumming Patterns
section_videos.video_description: Learn to play the open G chord – six strings. Learn and practice several strumming patterns. Learn to strum with your thumb or your first finger. Combine the G chord with other chords while strumming in various patterns. Guitar: Orangewood Ava Mahogany Live. D’Addario Strings.

section_videos.video_title: B5 Open Chord - A - Fingerpicking - Combine Chords

section_videos.video_title: B6 Open Chords - E A Em Am - Strumming - Muting
section_videos.video_description: Learn to play the Open E Chord – six strings. Learn to combine open chords: E A Em Am and others. Practice thumb muting and learn palm muting. section_videos.video_title: B8 Open Chords - 7 Progressions with 3 or 4 Chords

section_videos.video_title: Theory 01 C Major Scale
section_videos.video_description: Learning the elements of a Major scale, starting with C Major: degree, whole step and half step, and some attention to intervals and triads.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 02 G Major F Major
section_videos.video_description: Learning the notes in the G Major Scale and the F Major Scale, using what we learned in the preceding lesson.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 03 Roman Numerals
section_videos.video_description: Understanding the Roman Numeral system. What does I IV V mean, in C Major and G Major?

section_videos.video_title: Theory 04 D Major D Dorian
section_videos.video_description: D Major & D Dorian. Learning the notes in the D Major Scale. Learning D Dorian (by note and degree) and understanding its relationship to C Major.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 05 G Mixolydian C Mixolydian
section_videos.video_description: Learn the notes and degrees of G Mixolydian and C Mixolydian, understand their relationship to C Major, and play over a two-chord (I IV) vamp.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 06 A Aeolian
section_videos.video_description: Learn the Aeolian mode/scale (natural minor scale) by note and degree, understand the relationship between A Aeolian and C Major, and play over chord changes.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 07 Lydian
section_videos.video_description: Learn the Lydian mode/scale and play over chord changes in several keys. Gear: Ibanez AZ 2204 Custom, Air Straps guitar strap, Fender Pro Reverb (2), Lehle P-Split high-impedance signal splitter, D’Addario Strings, Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature, BOSS RC-1 Loop Station.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 08 Phrygian
section_videos.video_description: Phrygian mode/scale. Play a melody over chord changes, and discover the three other modes/scales that are played in melodic soloing over a four-chord progression. Gibson (1967) ES-335. Lehle P-Split High-Impedance Signal Splitter. Two Fender Pro Reverb Amps. BOSS RC-1 Loop Station. D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature Pick.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 09 C Major Pentatonic
section_videos.video_description: Major Pentatonic Scale. Learn the C Major Pentatonic (5-tone) scale by note and degree, understand its relationship to the C Major scale, and mix in a bit of Ear Training. Gibson (1967) ES-335. Lehle P-Split. 2 Fender Pro Reverb Amps. D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature Pick.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 10 Minor Pentatonic
section_videos.video_description: Minor Pentatonic Scales. Learn the A minor pentatonic scale, by note and degree, and understand its relationship to the A minor scale. Learn the C minor pentatonic scale, by note and degree. Gibson (1967) ES-335. Lehle P-Split. 2 Fender Pro Reverb Amps. D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature Pick. BOSS RC-1 Loop Station.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 11 Minor Triads
section_videos.video_description: Minor triads. Learn the relationship between major and minor triads. Learn C minor triads and F minor triads. Play the chord changes of a famous tune, using only triads. Improvise by following the triads. Gibson 2002 Les Paul R9. Lehle P-Split. Fender Pro Reverb Amps (2). D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature Pick.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 12 Diatonic Triads
section_videos.video_description: Learn diatonic triads in C Major. Then learn these triads in Bb Major, F Major and G Major. Once you are comfortable with the first two segments of this lesson, learn to use diatonic triads when improvising in D Dorian and G Mixolydian. Ibanez AZ 2204 Custom. Lehle P-Split High-Impedance Signal Splitter. Fender Pro Reverb Amps (2). D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature. BOSS RC-1 Loop Station.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 13 Diatonic 7th Chords
section_videos.video_description: Four-Note 7th Chords: Diatonic 7th Chords. Learn to play diatonic 7th chords in C Major, Bb Major, G Major and F Major. Guitar: Gibson 2002 Les Paul R9. Lehle P-Split High Impedance Signal Splitter. Fender Pro Reverb Amps (2). D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature. BOSS RC-1 Loop Station.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 14 Locrian Mode
section_videos.video_description: Locrian Mode. Learn the Locrian scale/mode by degree, and play over a backing track. Guitar: Kanji TF Signature. Lehle P-Split High Impedance Signal Splitter. Fender Pro Reverb Amps (2). D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature Pick. BOSS RC-3 Loop Station.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 15 Harmonic Minor
section_videos.video_description: Harmonic Minor. Learn the Harmonic minor scale by degree, and understand the sound and feel as Tomo plays over ii V i backing tracks in A minor and D minor.  Guitar: Kanji TF Signature. Lehle P-Split High-Impedance Signal Splitter. Fender Pro Reverb Amps (2). D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature Pick. BOSS RC-3 Loop Station.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 16 Melodic Minor
section_videos.video_description: Melodic Minor. Learn the Melodic minor scale by degree, and understand the sound and feel as Tomo plays over two backing tracks. Kanji TF Signature. section_videos.video_title: Theory 17 Lydian b7
section_videos.video_description: Learn the Lydian b7 scale, also known as Mixolydian #11, the 4th mode of the melodic minor scale, by degree, and the sound and feel of this scale over chord changes. D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature Pick. BOSS RC-3 Loop Station.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 18 Altered Scale
section_videos.video_description: Altered Scale, also known as Super Locrian, the 7th mode of the melodic minor scale: learn this scale by degree, and its sound and feel over chord changes. section_videos.video_title: Theory 19 Mixolydian b9 b13
section_videos.video_description: Learn the Mixolydian (b9) (b13) scale, also known as Phrygian Dominant, the 5th mode of the harmonic minor scale, by degree, and learn the sound and feel over chord changes. section_videos.video_title: Theory 20 Whole Tone Scale
section_videos.video_description: Learn the Whole Tone Scale, as well as the sound and feel of this scale over bluesy chord changes and a funky groove. section_videos.video_title: Theory 21 Diminished Scale
section_videos.video_description: Learn the Diminished Scale, together with the sound and feel of this scale over chord changes. Ibanez AZ Custom. Lehle P-Split. Fender Pro Reverb Amps (2). D’Addario Strings. Pickboy 1 mm TF Signature. BOSS RC-3 Loop Station with BOSS Katana 50 Amp.

section_videos.video_title: Theory 22 Diminished 7th Arpeggio
section_videos.video_description: Learn Diminished 7th Arpeggios by degree, sound and feel. Learn how to apply them in a jazzy A Blues musical example. Ibanez AZ Custom. Lehle P-Split.
